&lt;h2 id="headline-1"&gt;
Introduction
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div id="outline-text-headline-1" class="outline-text-2"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Bellybrush Theme&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; is a CSS theme for styling &lt;em&gt;Teraum&lt;/em&gt; reference
books and other materials.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id="outline-container-headline-2" class="outline-2"&gt;
&lt;h2 id="headline-2"&gt;
Bellybrush Theme
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div id="outline-text-headline-2" class="outline-text-2"&gt;
&lt;div id="outline-container-headline-3" class="outline-3"&gt;
&lt;h3 id="headline-3"&gt;
Design Philosophy
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div id="outline-text-headline-3" class="outline-text-3"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;em&gt;Bellybrush Theme&lt;/em&gt; theme is based on my own &lt;strong&gt;Oats&lt;/strong&gt;, which is based
on another of my themes, &lt;strong&gt;Brutstrap&lt;/strong&gt; which claims to style content as
it&amp;#39;s constructed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
However, &lt;em&gt;Brutstrap&lt;/em&gt; is catered toward a rather stark aesthetic, to make
it more readily match the &lt;a href="https://brutalist-web.design"&gt;brutalism&lt;/a&gt; advocated by &lt;a href="https://naildrivin5.com/"&gt;David Bryant
Copeland&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Bellybrush CSS</title><link>https://emsenn.net/library/tech/domains/computing/domains/internet/domains/web-design/domains/css/domains/style-frameworks/domains/bellybrush/source_1/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://emsenn.net/library/tech/domains/computing/domains/internet/domains/web-design/domains/css/domains/style-frameworks/domains/bellybrush/source_1/</guid><description>&lt;div id="outline-container-headline-1" class="outline-2"&gt;
